solution.p:
For Simpson's Rule, we see that

  S_6 = \frac{2}{3}M_3 + \frac{1}{3}T_3 = 140.8 \text{ ft}
.

To estimate the average velocity on [0,1.8], we compute change in position divided by change in time.  Here, since v(t) is always positive, the car's change in position equals its distance traveled.  Hence,

  AV_{[0,1.8]} = \frac{s(1.8)-s(0)}{1.8-0} \approx \frac{140.8}{1.8} = \frac{740}{9} \approx 78.22 \text{ ft/sec}
.
